OBJECTIVE: To estimate the treatment and health care costs of HIV infection or 
AIDS in France during the era of highly active antiretroviral therapy (HAART).
DESIGN: We used a clinical database of HIV-infected patients to calculate the 
resource use and cost of care for different stages of HIV infection. Costs were 
incorporated into a computer-based, probabilistic simulation model of the 
natural history and treatment of HIV infection to estimate the lifetime cost of 
treating patients with HIV disease.
SETTING: A northern France HIV clinical cohort.
PARTICIPANTS: 1232 HIV-infected patients followed from January 1994 through July 
1998.
RESULTS: In the absence of an AIDS-defining event, the average total cost of 
